s have type array of `wchar_t` (that is, **wchar_t[ ]**).) This means that a string is an array with elements of type `char`. The number of elements in the array is equal to the number of characters in the string plus one for the terminating null character.  \n  \n## See Also  \n [C String Literals](../c-language/c-string-literals.md)"}